article.headline: S. Illinois 50, Louisiana Tech 36
article.story: RUSTON, La. (AP) -- Randal Falker had four blocked shots and 12 points, while Matt Shaw scored 15 to lead Southern Illinois past Louisiana Tech 50-36 Wednesday night. Southern Illinois (5-1) jumped to an early 9-0 lead four minutes into the game and defensively held the Bulldogs (1-4) to only six points, 22-6, with 6:00 on the clock in the first half. The Salukis took a 28-12 lead into the half. Southern Illinois' Jamaal Tatum came into the game averaging 15.5 points per game, but was held to just six on the night. The Bulldogs outscored Southern Illinois 24-22 in the second half, but it would not prove enough to win. Kyle Gibson led Louisiana Tech in scoring with 13 points, while Marcus Elliot finished with 11.
